  Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon A\to B]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon B\to A]]></fr:tex> be injections.
  Consider the composite
  <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[     \varphi  := \mathcal {P}(A) \xrightarrow {f_{!}} \mathcal {P}(B) \xrightarrow {\lnot _{B}} \mathcal {P}(B) \xrightarrow {g_{!}} \mathcal {P}(A) \xrightarrow {\lnot _{A}} \mathcal {P}(A)   ]]></fr:tex>
  By Knaster-Tarski fixed-point theorem, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\varphi ]]></fr:tex> has a fixed point <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex>.
  Now define
  <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[     h(a) =     \begin {cases}       f(a) & \text {if $a \in  C$,}\\       g^{-1}(a) & \text {otherwise.}     \end {cases}   ]]></fr:tex>
  This is the required bijection.
